Halve, peel and finely chop the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Place the @corn on the cob{2} upright on a #chopping board{} and cut vertically downwards to remove the kernels. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add three-quarters of the onion and cook until soft, ~{5%mins}. Add the sweetcorn, stir and cook until piping hot, ~{3-4%mins}. Add the garlic and the coriander stalks and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Now, add the @fajita seasoning{1%Mexican spice} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and cook until fragrant, ~{2%mins}.

> TIP: If you're not keen on spice, don't add all the fajita seasoning!

Taste your mixture and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, remove from the heat. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} in a #colander{} and pop in a #mixing bowl{}. Roughly mash the beans with a #potato masher{} or #fork{}, then stir in the sweetcorn mixture along with the cheese and half the coriander. Taste to check the seasoning and add more salt and pepper if needed.

To make the quesadillas, lay out the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} and divide the bean mixture evenly between them. Spread it out over half of each tortilla then fold the other half over to make semicircular 'sandwiches'. Set them aside for a minute whilst you get on with the tomato salsa and citrus sour cream!

== Tomato Salsa ==

Chop the @vine tomatoes{2}(chopped into 1cm chunks) and finely slice the @baby gem lettuce{1/2}, then combine with the remaining coriander in a mixing bowl.

== Citrus Sour Cream ==

Zest and juice the @lime{1}. Add half the lime juice and the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season well with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Put the @sour cream{1%tub} in a #small bowl{} and mix in the remaining lime juice. Season with salt and black pepper and add lime zest to taste.

== Assembly ==

Wash and dry your frying pan and put it back on medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Fry two quesadillas at a time until golden brown, about ~{4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Keep them warm underneath some foil on a plate while you cook the rest.

Serve with the tomato salsa and citrus sour cream and let everyone help themselves. Enjoy!